%N A397161 Decimal expansion of the small face angle, in radians, of a canonical (dual-uniform) tetragonal trapezohedron.
%C A397161 The tetragonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the square antiprism.
%C A397161 Its faces are kites with one acute angle (this constant) and three obtuse angles (A397162).
%H A397161 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397161/b397161.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
